gmx:name.gco:CharacterString: Feature catalog for United States Census Block Groups, 2010

gfc:definition.gco:CharacterString: The polygons represent the U.S. Census block groups within the United States. A block group is a combination of census blocks that is a subdivision of a census tract, and is generally defined to contain between 600 and 3,000 people. A block group consists of all blocks whose numbers begin with the same digit in a given census tract. For the 2010 Census, a block group value of 0 for the water portion can be delineated in any census tract and not just those census tracts also defined to only include water area.
